# RandumbRadar v2.0.0

This release represents a complete overhaul of RandumbRadar and replaces the original version with a much more polished, reliable and feature-rich experience.

## ✨ New Features

### Completely Redesigned Radar Engine

* Brand new radar rendering engine.
* Smooth animated radar sweep.
* Improved radar grid with configurable colours.

### Aircraft Display

* Multiple aircraft display styles:

  * Dot
  * Triangle
  * Aircraft silhouette
* New aircraft silhouette based on a custom sprite.
* Aircraft now rotate to match their real-world heading using OpenSky `true_track`.
* Improved aircraft glow rendering.

### WiFi Setup

* Completely redesigned WiFi onboarding experience.
* Dropdown list of nearby WiFi networks.
* Manual SSID entry still supported.
* Password visibility toggle.
* WiFi reset option added to the web interface.
* Hold the ESP32 **BOOT** button for 5 seconds to erase WiFi credentials and return to setup mode without reflashing the firmware.

### OpenSky Configuration

* Separate OpenSky configuration stage after WiFi setup.
* Credentials stored permanently in flash memory.
* Improved connection handling and validation.

### Radar Customisation

* Configurable radar colours.
* Configurable radar sweep colour.
* Sweep animation can be enabled or disabled.
* Aircraft display style selection.
* Callsign visibility toggle.

### Performance Improvements

* Major rendering optimisations.
* Improved sprite handling.
* Reduced screen redraws.
* Background OpenSky polling to keep the radar animation responsive.
* Time-based radar sweep for smoother animation.
* Numerous memory and code optimisations.

### UI Improvements

* Larger boot logo.
* Improved setup screens.
* Cleaner web interface.
* Better page layout throughout.
* Consistent colour theme.
* Improved navigation between configuration pages.

### Reliability

* Improved WiFi reconnection handling.
* More robust configuration storage.
* Better error handling.
* Safer startup sequence.
* Multiple bug fixes and stability improvements.
  
## Breaking Changes

* This release supersedes the original beta builds.
* Existing users are recommended to perform a clean install using the Web Flasher.
* WiFi and OpenSky credentials will need to be entered again after a clean install.
